---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Panjastra Homam | Five Divine Weapons Ritual | Nagayakshi Temple">

  <section class="pooja-hero">
    <div class="pooja-hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="pooja-hero-content">
      <span class="pooja-badge">Divine Protection Ritual</span>
      <h1>Panjastra Homam</h1>
      <p class="pooja-tagline">Sacred fire ceremony invoking Lord Vishnu's five divine weapons for complete protection from all dangers, enemies, and negative forces</p>
      <div class="pooja-quick-info">
        <div class="quick-info-item">
          <span class="info-label">Frequency</span>
          <span class="info-value">Monthly / As Required</span>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-info-item">
          <span class="info-label">Duration</span>
          <span class="info-value">3–4 Hours</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="https://forms.gle/C3eQViaTHURBS48v7" class="btn-primary-gold" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Enquire</a>
        <a href="#details" class="btn-secondary-outline">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pooja-section" id="details">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>What is Panjastra Homam?</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <p class="intro-text">
            The Panjastra Homam is a powerful protective fire ceremony dedicated to the five celestial weapons of Lord Vishnu—Sudarshana Chakra (the divine discus), Panchajanya Shankha (the sacred conch), Kaumodaki Gada (the mighty mace), Nandaka Khadga (the invincible sword), and Saranga Dhanush (the cosmic bow). Each weapon represents a distinct aspect of divine protection and is worshipped as a living consciousness that serves Lord Vishnu. This homam creates an impenetrable shield of divine energy around the devotee, offering protection from all forms of danger—physical threats, legal troubles, black magic, enemies, accidents, and negative planetary influences.
          </p>
          <h3>The Five Divine Weapons Explained</h3>
          <p>
            According to Vishnu Purana and other sacred texts, these five weapons are not mere objects but enlightened beings who have taken the form of instruments to serve the Lord. The Sudarshana Chakra cuts through all obstacles and destroys enemies with the brilliance of a million suns. Panchajanya announces victory and dispels fear with its divine sound. Kaumodaki crushes the pride of demons and negative forces. Nandaka severs internal and external enemies with its sharp edge. Saranga maintains dharma and ensures cosmic balance. When invoked together through this homam, they form an all-encompassing protective force field that no adversity can penetrate.
          </p>
          <div class="variant-cards">
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>1. Standard Panjastra Homam</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>For:</strong> General protection and fear removal<br>
                <strong>Includes:</strong> Fire offerings to all five weapons, recitation of Panchayudha Stotram 108 times, and protective prasadam blessing
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>2. Enemy Removal Variant</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>For:</strong> Protection from known enemies and adversaries<br>
                <strong>Includes:</strong> Extended Sudarshana and Nandaka worship with special mantras for destroying opposition and ensuring victory in conflicts
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>3. Complete Protection Package</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>For:</strong> Comprehensive life protection and removal of all fears<br>
                <strong>Includes:</strong> Three-day homam with 1,008 mantra repetitions per weapon per day, consecration of protective amulets, and ongoing divine armor
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="info-box">
            <h4>Quick Facts</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Ancient Vishnu protection ritual</li>
              <li>Mentioned in Vedic scriptures</li>
              <li>Creates divine protective shield</li>
              <li>Removes all types of fear</li>
              <li>Can be performed any day</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box highlight">
            <h4>Best For</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Enemy troubles &amp; opposition</li>
              <li>Legal cases &amp; court matters</li>
              <li>Black magic &amp; evil eye</li>
              <li>Nightmares &amp; paranormal issues</li>
              <li>Accident-prone situations</li>
              <li>Travel safety</li>
              <li>Physical threats</li>
              <li>Phobias &amp; chronic fear</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tradition-section">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Divine Arsenal</span>
        <h2>The Sacred Weapons of Lord Vishnu</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="tradition-story">
        <div class="story-image">
          <img src="/images/Noorum%20Paalum.jpeg" alt="Panjastra Homam fire ritual">
        </div>
        <div class="story-content">
          <h3>The Living Consciousness of Divine Weapons</h3>
          <p>
            In Vedic cosmology, Lord Vishnu's weapons are not inanimate objects but highly evolved spiritual entities who have chosen to serve the Lord in this form. The Sudarshana Chakra is described in texts as having been crafted by Vishwakarma from the radiance of the Sun itself, containing the power of twelve million suns. The Panchajanya conch was obtained after Lord Krishna defeated the demon Panchajana who had taken refuge inside it. Each weapon has its own consciousness, mantra, and specific domain of protection.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Panchayudha Stotram, an ancient hymn that forms the core of this homam, addresses each weapon as a great sage (mahatma) in service to Vishnu. By invoking these weapons through fire offerings and mantra recitation, the devotee essentially requests these divine beings to extend their protection to them. The weapons respond by creating an energetic shield around the devotee that repels negative forces just as Lord Vishnu's weapons protected him during his incarnations on Earth.
          </p>
          <div class="scripture-quote">
            <p>
              &#8220;Those who daily recite this prayer to the five weapons of Lord Vishnu in the morning hours shall be rid of all sorrows and fears. Their sins shall be destroyed and pleasures established. In forest, in war, among enemies, or surrounded by water or fire—if the worried person reads this prayer with unwavering mind, they shall be happy, for this provides all-round protection.&#8221;
            </p>
            <span class="quote-attribution">&#8212; Panchayudha Stotram, Phala Shruti (Benefits Section)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tradition-variants">
        <h3>Understanding Each Divine Weapon</h3>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>Sudarshana Chakra: The Discus of Cosmic Order</h4>
          <p>
            The Sudarshana Chakra is the most powerful of all weapons, with its thousand sharp edges representing the thousand vents through which divine light destroys ignorance and evil. It spins eternally, creating a field of protection that no negative force can penetrate. When invoked in the homam, Sudarshana removes obstacles from all directions, cuts karmic knots, and destroys enemies visible and invisible. It is particularly effective against black magic, curses, and malevolent entities.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>Panchajanya Shankha: The Conch of Victory</h4>
          <p>
            The divine conch Panchajanya produces a sound that fills the hearts of devotees with courage while instilling terror in the hearts of enemies and demons. Its pure white radiance, compared to the brilliance of a million moons, represents purity and divine proclamation. When worshipped in the homam, Panchajanya removes all fear, announces the devotee's victories before they occur, and ensures that the devotee's voice is heard and respected in all matters.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>Kaumodaki Gada: The Mace of Strength</h4>
          <p>
            Kaumodaki, the golden mace the size of Mount Meru, represents pure concentrated force that crushes all opposition. Made from the bones of the demon Gadha, it symbolizes the transformation of negative energy into divine power. When invoked through fire offerings, Kaumodaki grants physical strength, mental fortitude, and the ability to overcome any opposition. It is especially beneficial for those facing powerful adversaries or seemingly insurmountable challenges.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>Nandaka Sword &amp; Saranga Bow: Precision and Dharma</h4>
          <p>
            The sword Nandaka cuts with precision, severing both external enemies and internal negative tendencies like doubt, fear, and attachment. The bow Saranga maintains cosmic balance by releasing arrows that never miss their target. Together in the homam, they ensure that the devotee's actions are both effective and righteous, aligned with dharma. They remove obstacles to success while ensuring the path followed is the correct one.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="booking-cta-section" id="booking">
    <div class="booking-cta-container">
      <h2>Book Panjastra Homam</h2>
      <p>
        Ideal for those seeking divine protection from all dangers<br>
        Can be performed on any day—especially powerful on Ekadashi
      </p>
      <div class="booking-cta-buttons">
        <a href="https://forms.gle/C3eQViaTHURBS48v7" class="btn-primary-gold btn-large" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Enquire Now</a>
        <a href="tel:+919946373522" class="btn-secondary-outline">Call: +91 9946373522</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
.pooja-hero {
  position: relative; min-height: 70vh; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  background: linear-gradient(rgba(82, 14, 9, 0.75), rgba(82, 14, 9, 0.9)), url('/images/Noorum%20Paalum.jpeg') center/cover;
  padding: 8rem 2rem 4rem; text-align: center;
}
.pooja-hero-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: radial-gradient(circle at 50% 50%, rgba(212, 165, 116, 0.12) 0%, transparent 60%); }
.pooja-hero-content { max-width: 900px; position: relative; z-index: 10; }
.pooja-badge { display: inline-block; background: var(--laterite-red); color: white; padding: 0.5rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
.pooja-hero h1 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 4.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: white; margin-bottom: 1rem; text-shadow: 0 2px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5); }
.pooja-tagline { font-size: 1.35rem; color: var(--bg-alt); margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.pooja-quick-info { display: flex; gap: 2rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 3rem; padding: 1.8rem 2rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); backdrop-filter: blur(10px); border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2); }
.quick-info-item { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; }
.info-label { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #ffd285; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; }
.info-value { font-size: 1.15rem; color: white; font-weight: 600; }
.hero-ctas { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.pooja-section { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: var(--bg-base); }
.pooja-container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; }
.section-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.section-header h2 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); }
.content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
.content-main { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.9; }
.intro-text { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--laterite-dark); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
.content-main h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.9rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--laterite-red); margin: 2.5rem 0 1.2rem; }
.content-main p { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.variant-cards { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.2rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
.variant-card { background: var(--bg-alt); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--gold); }
.variant-card h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
.variant-card p { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
.content-sidebar { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem; }
.info-box { background: var(--bg-alt); padding: 1.8rem; border-radius: 10px; border: 2px solid #e8c9a0; }
.info-box.highlight { background: var(--laterite-dark); border-color: var(--gold); }
.info-box h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.info-box.highlight h4 { color: #ffd285; }
.info-box ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
.info-box li { padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem; position: relative; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.05); }
.info-box.highlight li { color: var(--bg-alt); border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }
.info-box li::before { content: '✓'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--laterite-red); font-weight: 700; }
.info-box.highlight li::before { color: var(--gold); }
.tradition-section { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: var(--bg-alt); }
.section-label { display: block; font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--saffron); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 3px; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; text-align: center; }
.tradition-story { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 420px 1fr; gap: 3rem; align-items: start; margin: 3rem 0; }
.story-image img { width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.15); }
.story-content h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.9rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.story-content p { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.4rem; }
.scripture-quote { background: var(--bg-base); padding: 1.8rem; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 4px solid var(--laterite-red); margin-top: 1.5rem; }
.scripture-quote p { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.25rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--laterite-dark); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
.quote-attribution { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); }
.tradition-variants { margin-top: 4rem; }
.tradition-variants h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 2rem; text-align: center; }
.variant-detail { background: var(--bg-base); padding: 2.5rem; border-radius: 10px; margin-bottom: 1.8rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--gold); }
.variant-detail h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.variant-detail p { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.booking-cta-section { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--laterite-red) 0%, #6b1f2b 100%); text-align: center; }
.booking-cta-container { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
.booking-cta-container h2 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: white; margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.booking-cta-container p { font-size: 1.2rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.95); margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; }
.booking-cta-container strong { color: #ffd285; }
.booking-cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 2rem; }
.btn-large { padding: 1.4rem 3.5rem; font-size: 1.15rem; }
@media (max-width: 1024px) { .content-grid, .tradition-story { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .pooja-hero h1 { font-size: 2.8rem; }
  .pooja-quick-info { flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
  .booking-cta-container h2 { font-size: 2.2rem; }
  .booking-cta-buttons { flex-direction: column; align-items: stretch; }
}
</style>
